    <h2>Club History</h2>
<p>
Real Madrid, founded in 1902, soared to prominence in the 1950s under President Santiago Bernabéu. The club clinched an unprecedented five consecutive European Cup victories from 1956 to 1960. Icons like Alfredo Di Stéfano and Ferenc Puskás propelled its rise. Recent years saw three consecutive UEFA Champions League titles from 2016 to 2018 under Cristiano Ronaldo and Zidane. Beyond victories, Real Madrid's cultural impact is profound, with a global fanbase and the iconic Santiago Bernabéu Stadium symbolizing its legacy. The club embodies resilience, determination, and excellence, inspiring millions worldwide</p>
